Mpho Raborife, News24The driver had to be extricated from the wreck. (ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein -&nbsp;A woman has died after the car she was travelling in collided with a truck along the N8 between Bloemfontein and Kimberley on Friday, paramedics said.The woman, who is believed to be in her late 20s, was found trapped inside her car about 40km outside of Bloemfontein, ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing Harduth said.She was removed from the vehicle and found to have sustained critical injuries. She was airlifted to a nearby hospital where she succumbed to her injuries while being treated, the spokesperson said.The cause of the accident was not known.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.